description: Palindromes with exactly 10 palindromic prime factors (counted with multiplicity).
links: Lars Blomberg, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..27, terms < 10^16.
example: The palindrome 28898289882 is a term since it has 10 factors 2 3^2 7^3 11^2 101 383, all palindromic.
author: _Patrick De Geest_, Jun 15 1998
